# Internal SDD / process artefacts (FR-024): untracked from version control but
# kept in the working tree — the planning/closeout workflow reads them locally.
# CONSTITUTION.md is deliberately NOT ignored (it is the tracked governance doc).
# review/ + retro/ exist both at the repo root and under specs/*/ — the leading
# slash anchors the root copies; the per-phase ones are covered by /specs/.
/specs/
/.sdd/
/CLAUDE.md
/review/
/retro/

# Internal PRDs + release/review audits: untracked but kept in the working tree
# (same rationale as the SDD artefacts above — process docs, not public-repo
# content). History is preserved; the planning/closeout workflow reads them
# locally.
/PRDs/
/CODE-REVIEW.md
/RELEASE-READINESS.md
/RELEASE-BINARY-SIZE.md
/constitution-review-report.md

# Ephemeral skip-report the model-registry refresh bin writes for the PR body
# (see .github/workflows/model-registry-refresh.yml). Never committed — the
# refresh commit stages only the registry asset — but ignored defensively.
/model-registry-skip-report.md

# Superpowers brainstorming design docs (process artefacts, kept locally).
/docs/superpowers/
